
<Lesson stage="3" page="6" type="Reading Check">
<APageParagraph activityIntroClip="uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3"  pencil="p3" skipIntro="true">
   <paragraph>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>   
      <sentence>
         <text>When a human heart comes to a stop the person dies.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>That is simply because the heart is a pump.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>If it stops, the body, which depends on that pump, also stops.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>It is this pump which keeps our blood on the move, from the end of each toe to the top of the head.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>   
      <sentence>
         <text>As blood circulates it collects carbon dioxide.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>This is the waste matter in the blood stream.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The carbon dioxide makes the blood darker as it is collected.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The blood then takes on the more purple color, and it is this that we can see showing in our veins.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>   
      <sentence>
         <text>The blood returns to the right chamber of the heart, from where it is pumped to the lungs for cleaning.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
       <sentence>
         <text>Then it carries on to the left chamber of the heart.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>From there the clean blood is pumped out once more to circulate around the body.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>This constant pumping and cleaning goes on without a stop until we die.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
  </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>More and more people now live to be 100 years old.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>That means their hearts have been pumping non-stop for a century.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>We can only wonder when a computer will be built that can last that long!</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
</APageParagraph>
</Lesson>
